                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d192">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">390.1115A/12–1344: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Appointed Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hurley</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-19T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >December 19, 1944—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1670. Department was not aware that American citizens are required to obtain exit
                    permits from the Chinese authorities (ReEmbs 2012, December 13, 11 a.m.) and
                    would therefore appreciate receiving by telegram pertinent information
                    concerning permits together with summary of the regulations governing their
                    issuance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
